articles.title: Data
articles.contents:
This graph shows that total number of deaths from the years 1982 to 2019. The graph shows the total deaths for the ages 16,18,21 and 30 and above. Each graph also shows how much of the total deaths are caused by having a blood alchohol concentration(bac) of 0.08 or higher, otherwise known as drinking and driving.

articles.title: Alcohol Related Motor Deaths
articles.description: Relationship between age groups and the amount of Alcohol related deaths compared to Total amount of deaths
articles.contents:
Context:
As someone who recently started driving, the first question that pops up for a new driver is “Am I doing anything wrong?” As countless driving courses for teens and beginner drivers preach, Do Not Drink and Drive. These lessons may be effective for some time, but are they still in the driver’s mind after a couple of years?
Goal:
The goal is to find out if people who are older get into more crashes because of Alcohol, or we still need to solely educated novice drivers about drinking and driving. Are teens the only age group where they are vulnerable to drink and drive, or are other groups more vulnerable? This project aims to answer that question.
